H.P. 1198 - L.D. 1787
An Act to Increase Seed Money Contribution Limits for Gubernatorial
Candidates Under the Maine Clean Election Act
Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
Sec. 1. 21-A MRSA ยง1122, sub-ยง9, as amended by PL 2007, c. 571, ยง10, is further
amended to read:
9. Seed money contribution. "Seed money contribution" means, for a gubernatorial
participating candidate, a contribution of no more than $250 per individual made to the
participating candidate, including the candidate or the candidate's spouse or domestic
partner. For any other participating candidate, "seed money contribution" means a
contribution of no more than $100 per individual made to a the participating candidate,
including the candidate or the candidate's spouse or domestic partner.
